<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="40" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1323,1270,1582]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,384,1270,1296]" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. The genus is characterized by the long first flagellomere and three flagellomeres (
<figureCitation box="[351,444,1311,1337]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1731,1755]" captionTargetBox="[294,1292,326,1696]" captionTargetId="figure-68@3.[294,1293,326,1706]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A, B. Peratrimera mexicana n. gen., n. sp. (A) Reconstructive drawing of antenna. (B) Reconstructive drawing of wing; FIGURE 2C. Ataenogera sp. Drawing of the wing (C = costa, cu­p = posterior cupital cell, m = medial cell, M = media, R = radius)." pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); the two notopleural macrosetae on the thorax (
<figureCitation box="[1020,1111,1311,1337]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="2.[264,369,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[299,1288,449,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-76@2.[299,1288,449,1744]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE. 1. Peratrimera mexicana n. gen., n. sp. (A) Photograph of the holotype. (B) Habitus drawing of the holotype (np = notopleural macrosetae, pa = postalar macrosetae, sa = supraalar macrosetae, sc = scutellar macrosetae)." pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
); the closed wing cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[337,349,1362,1383]" fontSize="9" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">3</subScript>
; the setae on R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[536,548,1362,1383]" fontSize="9" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">1</subScript>
and R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[625,661,1362,1383]" fontSize="9" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">4+5</subScript>
(
<figureCitation box="[677,770,1351,1377]" captionStart="FIGURES 2" captionStartId="3.[264,382,1731,1755]" captionTargetBox="[294,1292,326,1696]" captionTargetId="figure-68@3.[294,1293,326,1706]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2A, B. Peratrimera mexicana n. gen., n. sp. (A) Reconstructive drawing of antenna. (B) Reconstructive drawing of wing; FIGURE 2C. Ataenogera sp. Drawing of the wing (C = costa, cu­p = posterior cupital cell, m = medial cell, M = media, R = radius)." pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); the vein C ending at M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1061,1073,1362,1383]" fontSize="9" pageId="1" pageNumber="40">2</subScript>
; the absence of a lateral macrosetae on the hind coxa; the short setae on the abdomen, the elongate shape of the abdomen; and the up­curved setae on the 8th abdominal sternite of the female (
<figureCitation box="[1191,1282,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE" captionStartId="2.[264,369,1771,1795]" captionTargetBox="[299,1288,449,1735]" captionTargetId="figure-76@2.[299,1288,449,1744]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE. 1. Peratrimera mexicana n. gen., n. sp. (A) Photograph of the holotype. (B) Habitus drawing of the holotype (np = notopleural macrosetae, pa = postalar macrosetae, sa = supraalar macrosetae, sc = scutellar macrosetae)." pageId="1" pageNumber="40">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
